{"seeAlsoSections":[{"generated":true,"title":"Architecture and Best Practices","identifiers":["doc:\/\/Forge\/documentation\/Forge\/ModularArchitecture","doc:\/\/Forge\/documentation\/Forge\/XcodePreviewSupport"],"anchor":"Architecture-and-Best-Practices"}],"metadata":{"modules":[{"name":"Forge"}],"roleHeading":"Article","role":"article","title":"SOLID Principles with Forge"},"hierarchy":{"paths":[["doc:\/\/Forge\/documentation\/Forge"]]},"primaryContentSections":[{"content":[{"level":2,"text":"Overview","anchor":"Overview","type":"heading"},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"Forge is designed to make SOLID principles the path of least resistance. Each","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"principle applies to both the framework’s internal design and how you structure","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"your own code when using it.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"anchor":"Single-Responsibility-Principle","level":2,"type":"heading","text":"Single Responsibility Principle"},{"name":"Note","style":"note","type":"aside","content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Each type should have one reason to change."}]}]},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"strong","inlineContent":[{"text":"In the framework:","type":"text"}]},{"type":"text","text":" Every Forge type does one thing — "},{"isActive":true,"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/Forge\/documentation\/Forge\/Container"},{"type":"text","text":" manages"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"lifecycle and resolution, "},{"isActive":true,"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/Forge\/documentation\/Forge\/Scope"},{"type":"text","text":" describes caching behavior,"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"isActive":true,"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/Forge\/documentation\/Forge\/ContainerInject"},{"type":"text","text":" handles injection, "},{"isActive":true,"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/Forge\/documentation\/Forge\/OverrideBuilder"},{"type":"text","text":" handles test"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"configuration."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"inlineContent":[{"inlineContent":[{"text":"In your code:","type":"text"}],"type":"strong"},{"text":" Each container should own dependencies for exactly one module.","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"If a container grows beyond its module’s concerns, that signals the module has","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"too many responsibilities.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"code":["\/\/ Correct: one container per module","final class AuthContainer: Container, SharedContainer {","    static var shared = AuthContainer()","","    var authService: any AuthServiceProtocol {","        provide(.singleton) { AuthService() }","    }","}","","final class AnalyticsContainer: Container, SharedContainer {","    static var shared = AnalyticsContainer()","","    var tracker: any AnalyticsTrackerProtocol {","        provide(.singleton) { MixpanelTracker() }","    }","}"],"type":"codeListing","syntax":"swift"},{"anchor":"OpenClosed-Principle","level":2,"type":"heading","text":"Open\/Closed Principle"},{"name":"Note","style":"note","type":"aside","content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Open for extension, closed for modification.","type":"text"}]}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"strong","inlineContent":[{"text":"In the framework:","type":"text"}]},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"reference","isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/Forge\/documentation\/Forge\/Container"},{"type":"text","text":" is an "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"open class"},{"type":"text","text":". New containers extend it"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"by adding computed properties — you never modify the base class."}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"strong","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"In your code:"}]},{"text":" Change behavior by overriding at the container boundary, not by","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"modifying implementation types. A test that needs different behavior provides a","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"different factory:","type":"text"}]},{"type":"codeListing","syntax":"swift","code":["\/\/ Correct: extend at the container boundary","try await AuthContainer.shared.withOverrides {","    $0.override(\"authService\") { MockAuthService() }","} run: {","    \/\/ test code...","}","","\/\/ Incorrect: adding test flags inside production types","class AuthService {","    var isTesting = false  \/\/ Don't do this","}"]},{"level":2,"type":"heading","anchor":"Liskov-Substitution-Principle","text":"Liskov Substitution Principle"},{"type":"aside","content":[{"inlineContent":[{"text":"Subtypes must be substitutable for their base types.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}],"name":"Note","style":"note"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"In the framework:"}],"type":"strong"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/Forge\/documentation\/Forge\/Container","type":"reference"},{"text":" subclasses are always valid containers. The","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"base class API works identically on any subclass.","type":"text"}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"In your code:"}],"type":"strong"},{"text":" Always declare container properties using protocol return types.","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"This is what makes mocks substitutable for live implementations:","type":"text"}]},{"type":"codeListing","syntax":"swift","code":["\/\/ Correct: protocol return type — mock is substitutable","public var authService: any AuthServiceProtocol {","    provide(.singleton) { AuthService() }","}","","\/\/ Incorrect: concrete type — cannot substitute a mock","public var authService: AuthService {","    provide(.singleton) { AuthService() }","}"]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"When the return type is a protocol, any conforming type — live or mock — can be"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"swapped in without changing consuming code."}]},{"level":2,"type":"heading","anchor":"Interface-Segregation-Principle","text":"Interface Segregation Principle"},{"style":"note","name":"Note","content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Clients should not depend on interfaces they do not use.","type":"text"}]}],"type":"aside"},{"inlineContent":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"In the framework:"}],"type":"strong"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"isActive":true,"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/Forge\/documentation\/Forge\/SharedContainer"},{"text":" is a minimal protocol with a single","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"requirement (","type":"text"},{"code":"static var shared","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":"). ","type":"text"},{"isActive":true,"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/Forge\/documentation\/Forge\/Container"},{"text":" does not conform to it by","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"default — you opt in only when you need the zero-argument ","type":"text"},{"code":"@Inject","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" syntax.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"strong","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"In your code:"}]},{"type":"text","text":" Define narrow protocols for each dependency. A"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"NetworkClientProtocol"},{"type":"text","text":" should not carry authentication methods just because the"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"networking layer also handles auth:"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"syntax":"swift","code":["\/\/ Correct: narrow protocols","protocol NetworkClientProtocol {","    func request<T: Decodable>(_ endpoint: Endpoint) async throws -> T","}","","protocol AuthTokenProviderProtocol {","    var currentToken: String? { get }","}","","\/\/ Incorrect: fat protocol","protocol NetworkClientProtocol {","    func request<T: Decodable>(_ endpoint: Endpoint) async throws -> T","    var currentToken: String? { get }   \/\/ Not a networking concern","    func logout()                        \/\/ Definitely not networking","}"],"type":"codeListing"},{"level":2,"text":"Dependency Inversion Principle","anchor":"Dependency-Inversion-Principle","type":"heading"},{"style":"note","content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"High-level modules should not depend on low-level modules. Both should depend"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"on abstractions."}]}],"name":"Note","type":"aside"},{"inlineContent":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"This is Forge’s entire purpose."}],"type":"strong"},{"text":" The container is the composition root — the","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"only place where abstractions are wired to concrete implementations. Everything","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"above it (ViewModels, services) depends only on protocols. Everything below it","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"(concrete implementations) knows nothing about the container.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"syntax":null,"code":["CoreProtocols (protocols only — no Forge import)","       ^","       |","Feature modules (depend on protocols, use Forge for wiring)","       ^","       |","App target (imports both, wires at startup)"],"type":"codeListing"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"ViewModels and services never "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"import"},{"type":"text","text":" a concrete implementation module directly."},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"They inject via protocol. The container handles the wiring:"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"syntax":"swift","code":["\/\/ ViewModel depends only on the protocol","final class LoginViewModel: ObservableObject {","    @Inject(\\.authService) private var authService","    \/\/ LoginViewModel has no idea what AuthService is —","    \/\/ it only knows AuthServiceProtocol","}"],"type":"codeListing"},{"level":2,"type":"heading","text":"Summary","anchor":"Summary"},{"rows":[[[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Principle"}]}],[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Forge Pattern"}]}]],[[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Single Responsibility"}]}],[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"One container per module","type":"text"}]}]],[[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Open\/Closed"}]}],[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Override at the container, don’t modify types","type":"text"}]}]],[[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Liskov Substitution","type":"text"}]}],[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Protocol return types on all properties","type":"text"}]}]],[[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Interface Segregation","type":"text"}]}],[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Narrow protocols, opt-in ","type":"text"},{"code":"SharedContainer","type":"codeVoice"}]}]],[[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Dependency Inversion","type":"text"}]}],[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Container is the composition root","type":"text"}]}]]],"type":"table","header":"row"}],"kind":"content"}],"identifier":{"interfaceLanguage":"swift","url":"doc:\/\/Forge\/documentation\/Forge\/SOLIDPrinciples"},"schemaVersion":{"minor":3,"patch":0,"major":0},"kind":"article","variants":[{"paths":["\/documentation\/forge\/solidprinciples"],"traits":[{"interfaceLanguage":"swift"}]}],"sections":[],"abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"How each SOLID principle maps to Forge usage, with practical Swift examples."}],"references":{"doc://Forge/documentation/Forge/Container":{"role":"symbol","fragments":[{"text":"class","kind":"keyword"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"text":"Container","kind":"identifier"}],"na